# SustainaBuy V2.0 Walkthrough

We have successfully upgraded **SustainaBuy** to a fully data-driven application with user persistence.

## New Feature Highlights

### 1. Persistence & Firestore
- **Real Database**: Replaced mock data with Google Firestore.
- **Dynamic Fetching**: Products are now loaded live from the database.

### 2. User Account System
- **Profile Dashboard**: View sustainability impact stats/gamification.
- **Wishlist**: Save favorite products to your permanent collection ([app/wishlist/page.tsx](file:///C:/Users/sarbr/Desktop/Antigravity/Projects/SustainaBuy_v0.2/app/wishlist/page.tsx)).
- **Secure Access**: Protected routes enforce login for personal features.

### 3. Automatic Product Scanner
- **"Scan to Add"**: New feature ([app/add-product/page.tsx](file:///C:/Users/sarbr/Desktop/Antigravity/Projects/SustainaBuy_v0.2/app/add-product/page.tsx)) allowing users to input *any* product name.
- **AI Simulation**: The system "finds" the product, generates a sustainability score, and saves it to the global database instantly.

### 4. Advanced Comparison
- **Side-by-Side**: Compare products on price, score, materials, and certifications ([app/compare/page.tsx](file:///C:/Users/sarbr/Desktop/Antigravity/Projects/SustainaBuy_v0.2/app/compare/page.tsx)).

## Setup Update

The setup remains similar, but **Firestore is now required**:
1.  Ensure your Firestore database is created in the Firebase Console (Test Mode).
2.  If you want to test the **Scanner**, just go to `/add-product` and type a name like "Recycled Yoga Mat". It will appear in the main product list after scanning!

## Validation
- [x] **Auth**: Login persistent across refreshes.
- [x] **Database**: Products added via Scanner appear in the main list.
- [x] **Wishlist**: Items added to wishlist stay there after logout/login.
